  "texts": [
    "Another tool used in time series analysis to comprehend the correlation structure of a time series is the partial autocorrelation function (PACF) graph.",
    "The correlation between a time series and its lags is displayed using a PACF plot while accounting for the impact of shorter lags.",
    "After accounting for all shorter delays (i.e., 1 through k-1), the PACF at lag k is the correlation between the time series at time t and its lagged value at time t-k.",
    "The order of an autoregressive (AR) process can be determined using a PACF display.",
    "The order of a moving average (MA) process can be determined using a PACF graphic."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}